This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques (improved LSTM) and time series analysis (ARIMA) to predict traffic flow, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), systems and control (cs.SY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
